President Barack Obama has proclaimed March 2010 as American Red Cross Month. In his proclamation, he recognizes the American Red Cross for its assistance and comfort to communities affected by disasters. He urges all Americans to embrace their shared duty to prepare for emergencies and highlights the importance of organizations like the American Red Cross in ensuring community readiness and resilience. The President also acknowledges the generosity of ordinary Americans in contributing to humanitarian efforts, particularly in response to the earthquake in Haiti. He emphasizes the need for citizens to act out of common humanity and encourages Americans to support the work of service and relief organizations.